begin_memory_text: We talked about Prolific and any other survey sites or online money making things we use
middle_memory_text: We talked about where I lived  abroad and what it was like in Malawi
end_memory_text: We talked about Dallas, his friends moving to Dallas and what living in Dallas is like
rest_of_day_open: It's Friday and it's the start of the weekend so I think it will go very well. I don't have to work or think about work and I get to relax and do the things that I want to do. I am also going to be watching scary movies with friends.
critical_positive: We were both genuinely engaged and interested in each other. We asked questions of the other person and engaged and followed-up. We were both able to contribute to the conversation and lead it while also letting the other person take the time to talk. He was also great at keeping up the conversation.
critical_negative: Sometimes we accidentally talked over each other but I think that was a sound issue maybe due to his headset. Sometimes I wasn't sure if he heard me or if iI should repeat myself but other than that everything went very well and the conversation was fun to have and engage in.

begin_memory_text: Introductions along with talking about Prolific and making money online. Our trials with no shows and some other adventures she has had doing online work. Why she does online work.
middle_memory_text: Doing surveys online for money and not getting paid. Her playing games online and having them actually working for her. Where she lives and how covid has affected her enjoyment of doing day to day activities. Living in another country and the living conditions and food she was introduced to.
end_memory_text: Moving to my state and giving her a hard sell on Dallas over Houston TX. Talking about transit and living in the area along with the area features and then wrapping it up with some state fair talk.
rest_of_day_open: I have one final video call I can do with someone and it's a bit on the bitter side and less of the sweet. I have met some people at a time when it has been less common for me to have done so. I could say if it wasn't for covid I would have these situations more often but the truth of the matter is I don't go out of my way to talk to people. I know these are somewhat forced situations where we are told to interact but I feel relaxed with the idea of talking to someone in person more than I did before. I'm interested in the next person I get to meet but also a bit sad.
critical_positive: The person was pretty attentive, young, and open-minded. She had a personality and a warm smile that would put anyone at ease. Talking to her was fairly easy and we did share some common ground that made it easier to connect and establish talking points. I was pretty interested in what she had to say.
critical_negative: I know it sounds a bit silly but I have talked to 4 others before her and we all went over the time cause I couldn't stop talking to them. The only thing that I would point out as less favorable was I feel rushed to cover a broad amount of topics past the "hello my name is" "I live here" part of the conversation. I was only getting warmed up and it was time to say goodbye. I did get the impression she wasn't feeling me as much as I was her.
